WEBVTT

00:00.418 --> 00:02.861
We're in a series that we titled, Out of Nowhere.

00:05.265 --> 00:10.692
And the title of this message in this series is, The Spirit in Skill and Excellence.

00:10.712 --> 00:11.473
Here's what I believe.

00:11.493 --> 00:17.201
There is a lie that many believers have believed without maybe realizing it.

00:18.463 --> 00:21.567
It is the lie that only certain things are spiritual.

00:22.728 --> 00:24.150
We think preaching is spiritual.

00:24.291 --> 00:26.013
For some it is, for some it's a job.

00:26.694 --> 00:28.016
We think praying is spiritual.

00:28.436 --> 00:29.778
For some is, some it's just

00:29.954 --> 00:32.017
over and over again the same stuff.

00:32.037 --> 00:34.602
We think singing is spiritual, and these are spiritual things.

00:36.024 --> 00:47.162
But building, designing, leading, managing, creating, serving, working with your hands, we quietly classify those things as ordinary.

00:47.964 --> 00:50.808
They're not on the same ballpark.

00:50.828 --> 00:55.215
But God does not see your life in sacred or secular categories.

00:55.516 --> 00:56.818
He just sees your life.

00:57.634 --> 01:02.078
And what God sees is surrender, surrendering to Him.

01:03.019 --> 01:08.504
See, the Spirit of God does not just feel preachers, He feels people.

01:09.345 --> 01:13.909
The Spirit of God does not just anoint platforms, He anoints faithfulness.

01:14.690 --> 01:21.637
And one of the most surprising moments in all of scripture proves this, Exodus, chapter 31, verses one through three.

01:22.678 --> 01:27.442
Then the Lord said to Moses, look, I have specifically chosen

01:27.554 --> 01:32.539
Bizelah, son of your eye, grandson of her, of the tribe of Judah.

01:32.940 --> 01:42.189
Listen this, I have filled him with the spirit of God, giving him great wisdom, ability and expertise in all kinds of crafts.

01:42.209 --> 01:54.642
The first person in scripture explicitly described as being filled with the spirit of God was not a prophet, it was not a priest, it was not a king, it was a builder.

01:56.450 --> 01:59.214
God filled a man not to preach, but to build.

02:00.135 --> 02:02.378
The Spirit of God empowers skill.

02:03.119 --> 02:05.843
The Spirit of God empowers excellence.

02:05.863 --> 02:10.509
And the Spirit of God empowers work done for his glory.

02:10.529 --> 02:17.439
And some of you may have believed the lie that your work is just your job and it doesn't really matter.

02:17.719 --> 02:21.584
I've had people for years walk up and say, I only do this and I only do that.

02:21.644 --> 02:25.810
And I'm like, it's not a thing when you only do, it's something that God

02:25.890 --> 02:27.372
had put in your path to do.

02:27.412 --> 02:36.065
And you're as anointed as any preacher or worship or whatever, you want to call it, you have the same ability.

02:36.306 --> 02:39.791
You have the same Holy Spirit and God sees you the same way.

02:42.315 --> 02:46.762
But when work is surrendered to God, it does become worship.

02:47.343 --> 02:54.834
Colossians 3, 23, work willingly at whatever you do as though you were working for the Lord rather than for people.

02:55.394 --> 02:59.258
Whatever you do can become worship when it is surrendered to Him.

02:59.518 --> 03:01.360
Let me just talk about that for a moment.

03:01.380 --> 03:03.142
Whatever you do, you do is under the Lord.

03:03.162 --> 03:04.683
We don't work for people, we work for God.

03:05.504 --> 03:07.706
God is the one that opens doors and closes doors.

03:08.227 --> 03:11.650
And a lot of our doors are closing because we work for ourselves and we don't work for Him.

03:12.311 --> 03:15.874
We've never surrendered our life to Him and said, God, I'm just gonna be faithful.

03:15.934 --> 03:17.416
I'm gonna do the best I can.

03:17.756 --> 03:23.922
And then what you don't realize is God will give you, pull out other gifts in you that you don't even know that are there.

03:24.770 --> 03:25.792
Folks, let me just say this.

03:26.013 --> 03:28.719
I should not be standing here if you look at me in the natural.

03:29.761 --> 03:31.264
I wasn't the brightest kid in high school.

03:31.284 --> 03:32.267
All I want to do is finish.

03:32.607 --> 03:33.429
Get my diploma.

03:33.970 --> 03:34.311
That's it.

03:34.351 --> 03:35.494
I didn't care what grades.

03:35.554 --> 03:36.857
I just wanted to get it and get it done.

03:39.502 --> 03:40.765
I'm not the brightest or smartest.

03:40.805 --> 03:42.349
I'm probably not the best speaker.

03:42.730 --> 03:43.992
But here's what I've done.

03:44.032 --> 03:44.333
Learn.

03:44.373 --> 03:44.754
Learn.

03:44.898 --> 03:49.765
When I worked at UPS, when I refereed, I learned to be and do it as unto God.

03:50.025 --> 03:55.253
Regardless of my bosses, regardless of problems, man, we do it for the kingdom.

03:55.573 --> 03:56.635
We do it for God.

03:56.935 --> 03:58.457
And he used me in my route.

03:58.537 --> 03:59.579
I prayed with people.

03:59.659 --> 04:00.901
I believe God with people.

04:02.603 --> 04:02.943
Why?

04:03.024 --> 04:13.298
Because no matter what you're called to do, no matter what gifts are in you, what skills you have, God gave them to you and he wants to use them if you'll surrender them.

04:13.442 --> 04:18.467
to Him, He wants to use them and cause you to be the most successful person you could ever be.

04:18.507 --> 04:24.913
And we got to quit getting caught up in the worldly stuff that's really junk.

04:24.933 --> 04:28.657
You know, I've learned this over the years that people get mental health days.

04:31.980 --> 04:38.006
And I'm not saying people don't have mental issues, but most of the time they just use those to get out of work.

04:38.026 --> 04:41.970
There's so many things wrong for me with that.

04:42.818 --> 04:44.961
Moses probably needed some mental health days.

04:46.022 --> 04:47.624
God says, I'm killing all the Jews.

04:47.644 --> 04:49.326
He said, don't do it because they'll mock us.

04:49.587 --> 04:52.210
Then later on Moses says, would you please kill every one of them?

04:53.612 --> 04:55.133
I bet he needed a mental health day.

04:55.674 --> 05:01.161
Don't buy into the rhetoric and the ungodliness of the world and buy into those things.

05:02.282 --> 05:05.727
Let me address something else because we see our problems with it.

05:05.747 --> 05:06.908
Bringing dogs to church.

05:08.951 --> 05:11.474
I always thought the Holy Spirit was my comforter.

05:13.922 --> 05:15.325
Now I didn't realize there's service dogs.

05:15.345 --> 05:16.286
There's real service dogs.

05:16.326 --> 05:17.028
I've been around them.

05:17.508 --> 05:18.951
I've seen them with MS patients.

05:19.011 --> 05:20.233
I've seen them with blind folk.

05:21.976 --> 05:23.920
But this other stuff doesn't make any sense to me.

05:23.940 --> 05:25.382
I thought the Holy Spirit was our comforter.

05:25.623 --> 05:29.650
We get caught up in the world's fads and really ignorance in my opinion.

05:30.210 --> 05:34.274
And then we buy into him as Christians, we buy into God and what his word says.

05:34.714 --> 05:36.056
I will work as unto the Lord.

05:36.376 --> 05:37.817
I will do my job as unto that.

05:38.118 --> 05:42.922
We could all have days where we're hurting in that, but it's just what I've taught my team for years.

05:43.202 --> 05:47.587
When we walk on this stage, we are no longer about ourselves, we come here to serve.

05:48.608 --> 05:51.891
I guess because my friend died, I could have taken a mental health day.

05:52.772 --> 05:54.213
I didn't even think about something like that.

05:54.233 --> 05:55.514
That didn't cross my mind.

05:58.117 --> 05:58.617
Are you sad?

05:58.637 --> 05:59.538
Yes, I'm sad.

06:00.578 --> 06:03.522
But when you come up here, when you serve God, you do it as unto Him.

06:04.443 --> 06:05.545
You put all that aside.

06:05.585 --> 06:07.868
I'll pick that up when I walk back through that door.

06:09.830 --> 06:10.852
But not now, folks.

06:10.892 --> 06:13.175
This is what I'm trying to teach us and share with us.

06:13.415 --> 06:14.657
And I believe it's godly.

06:14.877 --> 06:17.701
You can't find any of that in the Scripture.

06:18.782 --> 06:20.504
Well, these people know, no, they don't.

06:20.524 --> 06:27.954
They're just trying to make us so dependent on them and the world and the government that we are never dependent on God.

06:29.378 --> 06:31.220
I had a lady walk up to me, she's sitting in here now.

06:31.981 --> 06:41.012
She walked up to me a little bit ago and said, hey, man, they said I had an aneurysm in my stomach area, and she goes, I went back and it's healed, it's gone.

06:41.472 --> 06:42.133
God did that.

06:42.213 --> 06:44.355
I'm like, wow, that's pretty incredible.

06:44.736 --> 06:49.722
I don't know where she's at, but you told me and it's in my mind, that's God is the healer.

06:50.282 --> 06:51.484
Can you have mental issues?

06:51.544 --> 06:56.850
Sure you can, but we can believe God and do what's right and whatever, but these

06:56.930 --> 07:01.296
and these things and people usually use them because they don't want to go to work.

07:02.657 --> 07:04.520
Well, I'm sick today and you're out skiing.

07:07.483 --> 07:09.826
That's not how Christians are supposed to do their job.

07:09.846 --> 07:10.888
Let me tell you something.

07:10.908 --> 07:13.852
The bosses may never know, but God knows.

07:14.913 --> 07:18.898
And if you want the blessing of God in your life, we all have to begin to work.

07:19.106 --> 07:20.027
as unto Him.

07:20.368 --> 07:21.670
You don't work for that company.

07:21.690 --> 07:22.992
You don't work for that boss.

07:23.012 --> 07:27.137
You work for God, and in doing so, you'll treat that company and that boss better.

07:28.660 --> 07:29.881
And that's the heart of God.

07:29.921 --> 07:37.953
Whether you like it or not, we can bind it all the secular stuff, the ungodly stuff, the world of psychology, which I think is so crazy in itself.

07:38.714 --> 07:39.735
Because here's what I know.

07:39.795 --> 07:41.498
They can never heal anybody.

07:43.000 --> 07:45.944
I'm not against it, but they can't heal anybody.

07:46.024 --> 07:47.186
Only God can heal.

07:48.002 --> 07:50.565
They just teach you to deal with whatever you're dealing with better.

07:51.687 --> 07:55.251
And there's nothing wrong with that as long as it doesn't become ungodly.

07:57.794 --> 07:59.296
We could all have bad days.

07:59.957 --> 08:02.380
When we go to work, we do it as under the Lord.

08:03.582 --> 08:04.783
We may have heartache at home.

08:04.803 --> 08:06.786
When we go to work, we do it as under the Lord.

08:07.546 --> 08:09.389
Even in your home, you do it as under the Lord.

08:10.791 --> 08:12.713
God was building something in Exodus.

08:12.853 --> 08:13.554
I bet I'm the

08:13.730 --> 08:17.815
I've not heard any other preacher talk about mental health days.

08:17.855 --> 08:20.818
But anyway, I'm not as smart as some of them probably.

08:20.838 --> 08:23.862
But God was building something in Exodus.

08:25.284 --> 08:30.670
He was building the tabernacle, the dwelling place of His presence.

08:30.690 --> 08:33.934
And God did not just give instructions.

08:33.954 --> 08:35.456
He filled a person.

08:35.816 --> 08:40.722
Exodus 31.4 says, to devise artistic designs

08:40.930 --> 08:43.633
to work in gold, silver, silver and bronze.

08:44.014 --> 08:46.877
The Spirit of God made him excellent.

08:47.678 --> 08:50.381
And excellence is not perfectionism.

08:51.062 --> 08:52.343
Excellence is honor.

08:52.764 --> 08:54.406
Excellence is not doing things perfectly.

08:55.066 --> 08:58.010
Excellence is honoring God in whatever you do.

09:00.032 --> 09:00.793
Whatever you do.

09:02.175 --> 09:06.880
Excellence does not, does says, or excellence says, God deserves my best.

09:07.781 --> 09:08.562
Excellence says,

09:08.706 --> 09:16.194
You are worthy of my full effort, not my leftovers, because excellence offered to God is worship.

09:16.775 --> 09:21.360
And some of the most spiritual things you will ever do will never happen on a stage.

09:22.321 --> 09:24.323
It will happen in your office.

09:24.343 --> 09:25.825
It will happen on a job site.

09:26.165 --> 09:27.487
It will happen in your home.

09:27.907 --> 09:30.610
It will happen when no one sees you, but God.

09:32.472 --> 09:37.938
That's when it all happens, because God builds his house through hidden faithfulness.

09:40.386 --> 09:45.333
People tell me, well, you're the pastor of the church, so maybe you're not sure agreed or you're just as important.

09:46.374 --> 09:50.340
I've always believed that because I couldn't do this if you didn't do that.

09:50.961 --> 09:54.245
The prayer team is so incredible to me.

09:54.966 --> 10:01.736
I love, that's one of the favorite parts of the service for me on any service is watching people come up and get prayer.

10:01.756 --> 10:01.996
Why?

10:02.296 --> 10:06.322
Because God's house shall be called the house of prayer.

10:12.450 --> 10:16.075
Zechariah 4.10 says, do not despise the day of small things.

10:17.357 --> 10:19.861
God rejoices in faithful work.

10:19.881 --> 10:22.144
God rejoices when you show up with integrity.

10:22.685 --> 10:25.909
God rejoices when you do what is right when no one is watching.

10:26.350 --> 10:28.713
Some of you feel spiritually insignificant.

10:29.194 --> 10:30.836
You feel like your life is ordinary.

10:30.856 --> 10:33.380
You feel like your contribution is small.

10:34.161 --> 10:37.746
But Bizel el teaches us something very powerful.

10:38.427 --> 10:40.690
God feels ordinary people.

10:40.866 --> 10:46.974
to do extraordinary things when they surrender what is in their hands.

10:48.736 --> 10:52.461
Whatever you have, you put it in the master's hands.

10:56.486 --> 11:00.731
I'm only up here because I think God felt bad for me.

11:02.513 --> 11:05.777
But seriously, I meet other preachers.

11:05.837 --> 11:06.759
We have a lot of them here.

11:06.799 --> 11:07.379
They're smart.

11:07.419 --> 11:09.522
They're just incredibly gifted and talented.

11:11.330 --> 11:15.314
And I'm like, God, I tell my wife all the time, why do you think God has us to be a part of this?

11:15.935 --> 11:17.096
Have the friends we have.

11:21.040 --> 11:22.442
The people we get to serve with.

11:24.764 --> 11:26.706
And the only thing I can think of is I just never quit.

11:28.628 --> 11:30.090
You don't have to be the most talented.

11:30.130 --> 11:31.411
You don't have to be the most gifted.

11:31.812 --> 11:33.574
You just have to be the most surrendered.

11:34.955 --> 11:36.457
And watch what God does in your life.

11:37.318 --> 11:37.778
Watch.

11:41.474 --> 11:42.916
And that brings us to surrender.

11:46.161 --> 11:52.029
Surrender is giving God full ownership of what He has already given you.

11:52.870 --> 11:57.897
Surrender means I stop living as the owner and start living as a steward, which is so hard for most people.

11:58.578 --> 12:01.843
Surrender means nothing in my life is off limits to God.

12:02.524 --> 12:04.907
God does not feel what you control.

12:05.308 --> 12:07.350
He feels what you surrender to Him.

12:08.412 --> 12:09.874
As long as you hold it,

12:10.178 --> 12:15.287
It stays limited to you, but when you surrender it, it becomes empowered by Him.

12:16.329 --> 12:19.375
That's why a lot of us are stagnated, we're frustrated.

12:19.815 --> 12:21.338
It's like our life's not going anywhere.

12:21.599 --> 12:25.025
You have to ask yourself, have I truly surrendered my life to Him?

12:25.385 --> 12:32.498
Or have I bought up, bought up, bought into all the secular things and the secular mindset and the worldly mindset and just like the world.

12:32.518 --> 12:34.642
I'm no different than anybody else.

12:35.330 --> 12:37.533
but or have I surrendered my life to God?

12:37.553 --> 12:43.340
The reason some of us aren't moving forward is not because God doesn't want you to, it's because you've never surrendered what you already have to Him.

12:44.642 --> 12:49.809
And if you would, you'd watch doors open that no man can close, and God would close doors, no man can open.

12:50.730 --> 13:03.346
If you just believed and realized no matter what your gift is, what your talent, what you own, you could be a business owner, you could be a sanitation person, you could be a builder, you could be a construction worker,

13:03.842 --> 13:04.623
You could be a plumber.

13:04.743 --> 13:08.628
Whatever it is, you work as unto the Lord.

13:09.189 --> 13:12.733
You surrender that all to Him and say, God, this is your business.

13:14.115 --> 13:15.557
And how does he know of God's business?

13:15.997 --> 13:17.159
Do you give from your business?

13:17.179 --> 13:18.360
Do you sow from your business?

13:18.380 --> 13:19.902
Do you tithe from the prophet?

13:19.922 --> 13:22.425
Not just whatever comes from the prophet of your business.

13:23.046 --> 13:24.608
Is it his business or is it yours?

13:25.028 --> 13:26.290
Now, you're the steward of it.

13:26.498 --> 13:28.981
But man, at times we gotta say, God, this is your business.

13:29.041 --> 13:30.043
I'm gonna do it as under you.

13:30.503 --> 13:32.827
I'm just gonna believe you for whatever.

13:33.247 --> 13:35.210
I'm just gonna be faithful and honor you.

13:35.510 --> 13:41.258
I'm gonna do it in excellence because when you honor God, you're doing things in excellence.

13:41.278 --> 13:49.329
Not because you're the best, not because you did it perfectly, but because you just honor Him and you realize who you're really working for.

13:51.792 --> 13:56.018
John 15.5 says, apart from me, you can do nothing.

13:57.410 --> 13:59.312
Everything you have came from Him.

14:00.254 --> 14:01.735
Your ability came from Him.

14:01.775 --> 14:03.618
Your opportunity came from Him.

14:03.938 --> 14:05.680
Your strength came from Him.

14:06.301 --> 14:08.924
So the question is not, is your work impressive?

14:09.525 --> 14:12.669
The question is, is your work surrendered?

14:13.330 --> 14:16.394
Because surrender work becomes sacred work.

14:17.034 --> 14:19.858
Galatians 6, 9, let us not grow weary of doing good.

14:20.194 --> 14:22.837
for a new season we will reap if we do not give up.

14:23.117 --> 14:24.058
Just don't give up.

14:24.198 --> 14:25.219
Keep pushing forward.

14:25.479 --> 14:26.981
Keep striving to do what's right.

14:27.261 --> 14:28.402
God, I'm working this under you.

14:28.442 --> 14:30.724
I know I get caught up with some of this stuff, but I'm going to work at it.

14:30.744 --> 14:31.866
I'm going to get better at it.

14:31.886 --> 14:36.030
I'm not going to get caught up with all the complaining and murmuring that the other employees do.

14:36.350 --> 14:37.611
I'm going to do what I know to do.

14:37.852 --> 14:40.534
And as an employee, you're not going to bat mouth all your employees.

14:41.455 --> 14:43.477
How can you lead people you don't believe in?

14:43.517 --> 14:46.060
We got to change our attitude.

14:46.320 --> 14:48.402
The business world doesn't know everything.

14:49.282 --> 14:52.888
They know some things, but God's Word knows everything.

14:53.849 --> 14:57.895
We treat people well with respect and kindness, then God will bless your life.

14:58.136 --> 15:02.843
You have grace and mercy on others, so God can have grace and mercy on you.

15:04.025 --> 15:06.308
Someone messes up in the kingdom we want to throw them out.

15:07.550 --> 15:08.592
We're the worst at it.

15:09.113 --> 15:10.174
We're worse than the world.

15:10.975 --> 15:11.717
Oh, he messed up.

15:11.757 --> 15:12.317
She messed up.

15:12.337 --> 15:12.818
They're no good.

15:12.838 --> 15:13.960
They can't be used of God.

15:14.280 --> 15:15.663
That's what I heard with David Swan.

15:16.884 --> 15:17.906
I don't know how you could

15:18.338 --> 15:22.764
Help him get in the ministry because our job is to restore human beings.

15:25.988 --> 15:31.515
And I've always believed this, God, if I have grace and mercy on people, you'll have grace and mercy on me because I need it.

15:33.818 --> 15:35.080
I get tired of the church.

15:35.721 --> 15:38.284
We're the most cannibalistic group in America.

15:39.666 --> 15:40.447
We eat our own.

15:41.929 --> 15:42.910
We should be picking them up.

15:44.392 --> 15:46.034
We should quit being busy bodies.

15:47.202 --> 15:48.363
getting another people's life.

15:48.424 --> 15:48.904
You don't know.

15:48.924 --> 15:52.228
I don't even know why I'm talking about this.

15:53.490 --> 16:01.319
Because I think guys, we have to have the heart of God and quit getting caught up in this religious stuff and start living the life God wants us to live.

16:02.261 --> 16:03.422
Let's be good to each other.

16:03.903 --> 16:05.184
If we mess up, we mess up.

16:05.304 --> 16:11.972
No one in here, nobody in here can say you've never messed up.

16:11.992 --> 16:12.433
Nobody.

16:14.716 --> 16:15.697
And I just can't stand it.

16:15.717 --> 16:16.498
I've never liked it.

16:17.858 --> 16:19.621
Even when I was young and low, I didn't like it.

16:19.681 --> 16:21.584
It was like something's not right here.

16:22.245 --> 16:23.427
We should help one another.

16:25.329 --> 16:27.693
We should believe for the best in one another.

16:30.778 --> 16:31.158
I don't know.

16:37.869 --> 16:44.219
We need to understand that some of you are building something right now and no one sees it.

16:45.260 --> 16:46.482
You're building your family.

16:46.978 --> 16:48.179
You're building your character.

16:48.219 --> 16:49.901
You're building your integrity.

16:49.941 --> 16:51.143
You're building your faith.

16:52.204 --> 16:53.205
It matters to God.

16:54.166 --> 16:57.450
Nothing surrendered to God is ever wasted.

16:58.491 --> 17:02.355
And then the tabernacle points us to Jesus.

17:02.596 --> 17:03.457
This is what's interesting.

17:03.817 --> 17:08.042
John 1 14, and the word became flesh and dwelt among us.

17:08.582 --> 17:11.085
Jesus became the dwelling place of God's presence.

17:11.826 --> 17:13.468
The tabernacle was a shadow.

17:13.948 --> 17:15.410
Jesus is the substance.

17:15.778 --> 17:18.682
And now through Christ, something even greater has happened.

17:18.702 --> 17:29.058
Listen to this, 1 Corinthians 6, 19, or do you not know your body is a temple of the Holy Spirit within you whom you have received from God?

17:29.098 --> 17:31.962
You are not your own.

17:32.503 --> 17:35.767
